						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Ellamma shrine in a field about 2 km east of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1719, Pingaḷa, Bhādrapada ba. 10,</hi> corresponding to 1797 A.D., September 16, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a temple and a tank by Narasōju, son of Bōchare Rangarāju Mannōju.</p>						

						</summary>
